---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="About — PixelMorph, The Image Converter That Doesn't Upload Your Files"
  description="About PixelMorph — a free image converter that runs entirely in your browser. What it is, who built it, and why we don't upload your images to a server."
  keywords="pixelmorph about, browser image converter, private image converter, client side image converter, no upload converter"
>
  <section class="page-container about-page">
    <header class="about-header">
      <span class="t-caption-mono eyebrow">About</span>
      <h1 class="t-display-xl">A converter that respects your files.</h1>
      <p class="t-body-lg sub">
        Most "free online" image converters route your images through their servers. We don't.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="about-body">
      <h2 class="t-display-md">The pitch</h2>
      <p class="t-body-md">
        PixelMorph is a free, fast, browser-only image converter. Drop in a PNG, pick JPG, get a JPG. No upload bar, no waiting on a server, no signup form, no daily quota, no ads draped around the workspace.
      </p>

      <h2 class="t-display-md">Why client-side?</h2>
      <p class="t-body-md">
        Modern browsers can decode and encode all of the formats we support natively — the Canvas API has handled PNG, JPG, WebP, and GIF for a decade, and small JavaScript libraries cover the long tail (TIFF, ICO). There's no technical reason to upload your image to a stranger's server to flip its extension, and several reasons not to.
      </p>
      <ul class="reasons">
        <li>
          <strong>Privacy.</strong> Your image data never crosses the network. We never see it, log it, or touch it.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Speed.</strong> Skipping the round-trip — upload, queue, process, download — wins back several seconds per file. On batches, it's enormous.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Reliability.</strong> Once the page loads, the converter works without an internet connection. No 502s, no rate limits, no maintenance windows.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Honesty.</strong> A site that uploads your photos for "free" usually pays for the servers in some other way — ads, data, the gradual conversion of users into a paid tier. Browser-side has no marginal cost, so it stays free.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="t-display-md">Roadmap</h2>
      <p class="t-body-md">
        Next up: HEIC, AVIF, BMP, EPS, and proper multi-frame GIF/animated-WebP encoding. After that: an opt-in "metadata viewer" so you can see exactly what EXIF a photo carries before you publish it.
      </p>

      <h2 class="t-display-md">Open the converter</h2>
      <p class="t-body-md">
        <a class="cta-link" href="/#converter">Convert an image →</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .about-page {
    padding-block: 64px 32px;
    max-width: 800px;
  }
  .about-header {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 16px;
    margin-bottom: 48px;
  }
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .about-page { padding-block: 40px 24px; }
    .about-header { margin-bottom: 32px; }
    .about-body h2 { margin-top: 12px; }
  }
  .eyebrow { color: var(--color-mute); }
  .sub { color: var(--color-body); max-width: 580px; margin: 0; }

  .about-body {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 16px;
  }
  .about-body h2 {
    margin: 24px 0 4px;
  }
  .about-body p { color: var(--color-body); margin: 0; max-width: 720px; }
  .reasons {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 8px 0 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 12px;
  }
  .reasons li {
    color: var(--color-body);
    line-height: 24px;
    padding-left: 16px;
    border-left: 2px solid var(--color-hairline);
  }
  .reasons strong { color: var(--color-ink); }

  .cta-link {
    color: var(--color-ink);
    font-weight: 500;
    text-decoration: none;
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 6px;
    padding: 12px 20px;
    background-color: var(--color-canvas-soft);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-hairline);
    border-radius: 999px;
    transition: all 0.15s ease;
  }
  .cta-link:hover {
    background-color: var(--color-ink);
    color: var(--color-on-primary);
    border-color: var(--color-ink);
  }
</style>
